commitResults.messageTitle: Adds Test Ensuring New Tag Addition on First Witness
commitResults.messageBody:
Add a test in AddCommandTest.java that ensures a tag will be added upon a new person addition through the add command if the tag does not already exist in the mapping.

Introduced ability to peek that the person's list through a completely protected unmodifiable observable list supported with deep copying.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Test Relating to Tag Uniqueness and Collection
commitResults.messageBody:
Exposes Immutable PersonList from Tag, via deep copying each Person object to maintain fully private access only

Adds test in AddCommandTest to check if model will add a newly witnessed tag to UniqueTagMapping when a Person is added
Adds test in TagTest to check that shallow copying will return equivalent lists of Persons and deep copying ensures complete immutability
Adds test in every field for Person that checks deep copying will create a new object, but equivalent in comparison, except for Tags which are shallow-copied (only copies the list of person, but does not make deep copies of each person; cyclical dependency between Tag and Person, deep copying may not be possible)
Adds Loan tests
